<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,436,567]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">
This genus currently contains some 
<number box="[553,581,436,460]" pageId="1" pageNumber="48" value="90.0">90</number>
named species but many others still await description. The majority of 
<taxonomicName box="[1378,1436,436,460]" class="Insecta" family="Lonchaeidae" genus="Silba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1378,1436,436,460]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">Silba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are associated with the tropical forests of Africa, Asia, and Australasia extending northwards into southern Europe, 
<collectingCountry box="[246,328,508,532]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[486,557,508,532]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="48">China</collectingCountry>
. Larvae have been reared from the fruits and stems of a wide range of tropical plants.
</paragraph>
